 ype": "highlight"\, "id": "b4413bba-8068-4825-bc86-e6a2c46bbe60"\, "shape"
 : "underline"\, "isFront": false\, "isAnimationEnabled": false\, "animatio
 n": "draw"\, "duration": 0.5\, "direction": "right"\, "color": { "type": "
 THEME_COLOR" }\, "thickness": { "unit": "em"\, "value": 0.1 }\, "linecap":
  "square" } ] Limited to 12 students Saturday March 38\, 2026\, 12:30 pm -
 3:30pm Tickets: $90 for Non-members\; $80 for members and students Class m
 aterials are not included. If you prefer the instructor provide your mater
 ials\, you have the option of paying an additional $30 (up until 10 days b
 efore the class).&nbsp\; In this lively workshop\, Dr. Liu will teach stud
 ents a unique form of watercolor integration with Chinese ink and oil past
 el. Students will also learn design\, composition\, shape\, line\, point\,
  value and color by painting natural objects. By using Chinese brush strok
 e and wet-on-wet techniques\, participants will explore the power of posit
 ive and negative paintings. They will also experiment with watercolor expr
 ession and abstraction with splashing\, dripping\, and Chinese calligraphy
  painting.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; The workshop will begin with an instructor demo\,
  followed by individual instruction and group discussion Dr. Qinqin Liu ha
 s taught watercolor workshops since 2017 at Yosemite National Park\, Sitka
  Art and Ecology Center\, and Chalk Hill Art Residency in California and O
 regon Coast. She has practiced ink painting and calligraphy in China since
  1974. When she came to the U.S.\, she studied with award-winning watercol
 orists Frank Webb and Professor Cheng-Khee Chee.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; Required Ma
 terials List:&nbsp\; ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Sketchbook (at least 5"x 8"
 ) ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Watercolor paper (Arches Cold press 140lb at l
 east two sheets 11x15) ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; 2 B and 6B pencils&nbsp\;
 &nbsp\; ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Palette for color mixing (e.g. a recycle
 d egg plastic container) ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Watercolor brushes (Pri
 nceton brand is good): Rounds sizes 6 and 10 or 12\; Flats sizes 1 ½” a
 nd larger ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Watercolor paints: 3 primary colors (e
 .g.\, Ultramarine Blue\, Azo Yellow\, and Cadmium Red or rose madder)\, op
 tional sap green\, and any of your favorite colors. ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbs
 p\; Two water containers (e.g.\, two empty yogurt containers). ·&nbsp\; &
 nbsp\; &nbsp\; Paper clamps\, a water spray bottle\, sponges\, and a paper
  towel. ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Masking tapes and boards to secure the w
 atercolor papers during the painting. ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Mr. Clean 
 Erasers (cleaning pads that you can buy in Walmart or other stores). ·&nb
 sp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Optional: masks\; your favorite natural objects and d
 rawings. Materials Provided by Instructor: ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Chine
 se ink and brush as well as oil pastels for class demo and limited uses. 
 ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Tissue paper\, plastic wraps\, and natural objec
 ts such as sunflowers&nbsp\; ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Watercolor painting
 s and sketch examples as well as class handouts.&nbsp\; #block-yui_3_17_2_
